Data.event_text: 5 January  The United States and Germany agree to send Bradley Fighting Vehicles and Marder infantry fighting vehicles to Ukraine. Germany will also supply the Ukrainian military with a MIM-104 Patriot surface-to-air missile system.

links.text: -"US and Germany agree to send infantry fighting vehicles to Ukraine". The Guardian. 5 January 2023. Retrieved 6 January 2023.-

Data.event_text: 8 January  North Rhine-Westphalia Police arrest two Iranian brothers in Castrop-Rauxel, Ruhr, North Rhine-Westphalia, on the suspicion of planning an Islamic terrorist attack using chemical weapons.

links.text: -"Iranian man held in Germany over suspected chemical attack". BBC News. 8 January 2023. Retrieved 8 January 2023.-

Data.event_text: 16 January  German Defence Minister Christine Lambrecht resigns from the Scholz cabinet amid criticism over her handling of the Russian invasion of Ukraine.

links.text: -"German defence minister resigns amid criticism, pressure over Ukraine arms". Reuters. Germany. 16 January 2023. Retrieved 16 January 2023.-

Data.event_text: 22 January  German Foreign Affairs Minister Annalena Baerbock says that Germany will not prevent Poland from sending Leopard 2 main battle tanks to Ukraine which Ukrainian officials say are pivotal to defeating Russian forces on the battlefield.

links.text: -Rinke, Andreas; Thomas, Leigh (23 January 2023). "Germany would not block Poland from sending tanks to Ukraine, minister says". Reuters. Retrieved 23 January 2023.-

Data.event_text: 24 January  German Chancellor Olaf Scholz decides to send Leopard 2 main battle tanks to Ukraine, and will allow other operators of the tanks, such as Poland, to do so as well.

links.text: -Alkousaa, Riham; Rinke, Andreas; Hansen, Holger; Stewart, Phil; Ali, Idrees; Siebold, Sabine (24 January 2023). Oatis, Jonathan (ed.). "Germany to send Leopard tanks to Kyiv, allow others to do so - sources". Reuters. Berlin; Washington. Retrieved 24 January 2023.-

Data.event_text: 25 January  Two people are killed and seven others are wounded in a mass stabbing on a passenger train in Brokstedt, Steinburg, Schleswig-Holstein.

links.text: -Fahey, Ryan (25 January 2023). "Knife attacker goes on rampage on train with two dead and seven injured". mirror. Retrieved 25 January 2023.-

Data.event_text: 10 February  At least 35 people are injured when a bus overturns near Magdeburg, Saxony-Anhalt.

links.text: -"Polish bus comes off German highway and overturns; 35 hurt". AP NEWS. 10 February 2023. Retrieved 10 February 2023.-

Data.event_text: 12 February  2023 Berlin repeat state election
22 February  Germany expels two employees of the Iranian embassy in response to Iran sentencing pro-monarchist dual German-Iranian Jamshid Sharmahd to death over a 2008 bombing in Iran.

links.text: -More, Rachel; Heine, Friederike (22 February 2023). Richardson, Alex (ed.). "Germany expels two Iranian embassy employees over death sentence". Reuters. Retrieved 22 February 2023.-

Data.event_text: 9 March  A mass shooting in Hamburg kills six people and injures eight others. The gunman then commits suicide.

links.text: -"Several killed in shooting in Germany city of Hamburg". BBC News. 9 March 2023. Retrieved 9 March 2023.-

Data.event_text: 911 March  Last meeting of Synodal Path in Frankfurt am Main
3 April  Four people are injured in a fire at a hospital in Berlin. One person has been arrested on suspicion of arson.

links.text: -"4 hurt in German hospital fire, suspect arrested". AP NEWS. 3 April 2023. Retrieved 10 April 2023.-

Data.event_text: 11 April  Germany expels the ambassador of Chad in a tit-for-tat decision following the expulsion of the German ambassador from Chad last week.

links.text: -"Germany expels Chad's ambassador in tit-for-tat move". Reuters. 11 April 2023. Retrieved 11 April 2023.-

Data.event_text: 15 April  The Nuclear power in Germany ends. The last three power plants Isar Nuclear Power Plant, Neckarwestheim Nuclear Power Plant and Emsland Nuclear Power Plant in Germany stop.

links.text: -Handelsblatt.com: „Atomkraft konnte die Versprechungen nie einlösen“ – Deutschland beendet das Kernkraft-Zeitalter (german)-
-Tagesschau.de: Nukleare Risiken bleiben (german)-

Data.event_text: 18 April  At least four people are severely injured in a stabbing attack at a gym in Duisburg.

links.text: -Dunne, John (18 April 2023). "Several people injured in attack at gym in German city of Duisburg". Evening Standard. Retrieved 19 April 2023.-

Data.event_text: 26 April   the Federal Office for the Protection of the Constitution BfV, after four years of investigations into the youth wing of the Alternative for Germany AfD party, categorized that group as a "confirmed" extremist organization. This allowed the chief of the BfV Thomas Haldenwang to place the youth wing of the AfD under even more intensive surveillance than the tapping of phone and the use of undercover agents than had been the case until then.
14 May  The SPD wins the 2023 Bremen state election with 29.8% of the vote.

links.text: -"Wahlsystem der Bürgerschaftswahl 2019 in Bremen (#HBWahl)". Wahlrecht.de (in German). Retrieved 7 May 2022.-

Data.event_text: 25 May  The German economy enters recession for the first time since the COVID-19 pandemic amid high levels of inflation.

links.text: -"Germany falls into recession as inflation hits economy". BBC News. 25 May 2023. Retrieved 25 May 2023.-

Data.event_text: 31 May  Trial of Lina E. a Dresden court convicts 4 far-left extremists of violent attacks against far-right individuals.

links.text: -"German Court Convicts 4 Leftists in Attacks Targeting Neo-Nazis". New York Times. 31 May 2023. Archived from the original on 1 June 2023.-
-"German Court Convicts 4 Leftists in Attacks Targeting Neo-Nazis". New York Times. 31 May 2023. Archived from the original on 1 June 2023.-

Data.event_text: 5 June  Björn Höcke, Leader of Alternative for Germany in Thuringia is charged for using Nazi slogan Everything for Germany.

links.text: -"Prominent figure in German far-right party charged over alleged Nazi slogan". ABC News.-
-"AfD politician Höcke charged with using Nazi slogan – DW – 06/05/2023". Deutsche Welle.-
-"Prominent German politician charged with alleged use of Nazi slogan". Fox News. 5 June 2023.-
-"German far-right politician charged over Nazi slogan". 5 June 2023.-

Data.event_text: 25 June  The Alternative for Germany wins its first district election in Sonneberg, Thuringia despite all other parties supporting the CDU Candidate.

links.text: -"Germany: Far-right AfD wins first governing post – DW – 06/25/2023". Deutsche Welle.-
-"Germany's far-right AfD party wins historic victory in local election". 25 June 2023.-
-"Germany's far-right AfD wins vote to lead district for first time". Reuters. 26 June 2023.-
-"German far-right party wins its first county leadership post as it rises in polls". ABC News.-

Data.event_text: 2 July  in a run-off election the AfD candidate Hannes Loth [de] won against the independent Nils Naumann in Raguhn-Jeßnitz Saxony-Anhalt, becoming the first ever AfD mayor.

Data.event_text: 24 July  CDU leader Friedrich Merz shows some willingness to work with the Alternative for Germany (AfD) party at the local level, which was interpreted as the erosion of the 'firewall' separating conservatives from the far-right, sparking intense backlash within his own party, notably from Kai Wegner, the current Governing Mayor of Berlin.

links.text: -Oltermann, Philip (24 July 2023). "German centre-right leader says he is willing to work with far-right AfD at local level". The Guardian. ISSN 0261-3077. Retrieved 24 July 2023.-

Data.event_text: 21 August  Germany's central bank announces the country's economy will be stagnant in the third quarter, due to high energy prices and rising borrowing costs.

links.text: -"German central bank sees the economy stagnating again in the 3rd quarter". AP News. 21 August 2023. Retrieved 11 September 2023.-

Data.event_text: 23 August  Germany passes legislation to ease citizenship rules, aiming to reduce a shortage of skilled workers and to improve the integration of immigrants.

links.text: -"Germany is moving forward with a plan to ease its citizenship rules as it seeks to attract workers". AP News. 23 August 2023. Retrieved 11 September 2023.-

Data.event_text: 24 August  A German federal court rejects an appeal by a military officer who posed as a asylum-seeker and was convicted of plotting to attack prominent politicians.

links.text: -"Court rejects appeal by German soldier convicted of plotting to attack politicians". AP News. 24 August 2023. Retrieved 11 September 2023.-

Data.event_text: 8 October  The CSU wins the 2023 Bavarian state election with 37% of the vote, with the Free Voters taking second at 15.8%, their best result ever.
8 October  2023 Hessian state election

links.text: -"Hessen: Aktuelle Wahltrends & Sonntagsfragen" (in German). Retrieved 18 August 2022.-

Data.event_text: 13 October  Mühldorf van crash Seven people are killed and 16 others injured when a severely overloaded vehicle carrying illegal immigrants from the Middle East crashes in Mühldorf, Bavaria.

links.text: -"7 killed and 16 injured as a van overloaded with migrants crashes in southern Germany". AP News. 13 October 2023. Retrieved 13 October 2023.-

Data.event_text: 16 October  German Chancellor Olaf Scholz announces he will visit Israel on Tuesday and then Egypt. The German Chancellor said on Monday that the visit allows him to "express his solidarity" with Israel.

links.text: -AFP and ToI Staff. "German leader Scholz says he'll visit Israel this week to 'express my solidarity'". www.timesofisrael.com. Retrieved 16 October 2023.-

Data.event_text: 18 October  Extremists throw Molotov cocktails at a synagogue in Berlin, Germany. Several antisemitic incidents in the country have been rising following the escalation in the 2023 IsraelHamas war. The incident is being investigated as a terrorist attack.

links.text: -"Berlin synagogue firebombed: Olaf Scholz condemns attack". POLITICO. 18 October 2023. Retrieved 18 October 2023.-

Data.event_text: 24 October  2023 North Sea incident Two cargo ships, the British-flagged Verity and the Bahamas-flagged Polesie, collide in the North Sea near the Heligoland islands, with several individuals missing and the suspected sinking of the Verity. Rescue efforts are underway.

links.text: -"Several missing after two cargo ships collide in North Sea". Firstpost. 24 October 2023. Retrieved 24 October 2023.-

Data.event_text: 30 October  AfD politician Daniel Halemba is arrested after Nazi salute complaints and possession of banned totalitarian symbols.

links.text: -"German politician held after Nazi slogan complaint". BBC News. 30 October 2023. Retrieved 30 October 2023.-

Data.event_text: 5 November  2023 Hamburg Airport hostage incident A hostage crisis caused by "family drama" halts flights at Hamburg Airport.

links.text: -Kappeler, Inke; Davis, A. J. (4 November 2023). "Hamburg airport hostage situation that caused suspension of flights has ended, police say". CNN. Retrieved 5 November 2023.-

Data.event_text: 27 November  German Catholic priest Hans-Joachim Lohre, who disappeared in Bamako, Mali, in  and was presumed kidnapped, is released by his captors and returns to Germany.

links.text: -German priest abducted in Mali in 2022 freed-

Data.event_text: 17 December  The AfD candidate for mayor of Pirna, Saxony wins, becoming the first mayor of a city with more than 20,000 inhabitants to be held by the Alternative for Germany.

links.text: -"Germany: Far-right AfD wins first city mayoral election – DW – 12/17/2023". Deutsche Welle.-
-Arnold, Martin (18 December 2023). "German far-right party makes electoral breakthrough". Financial Times.-
